</HEAD><BODY ALINK="#00CC00" LINK="#3C914D" VLINK="#005500" BGCOLOR="#CCCC99"><H1><a href="wiki.pl?HomePage"><img src="/forums/DoT_Sword.jpg" alt="[Home]" border=0 align="right"></a><a href="wiki.pl?search=Page+Viewer+Controls">Page Viewer Controls</a></H1><a href="wiki.pl?HomePage">HomePage</a> | <a href="wiki.pl?RecentChanges">RecentChanges</a> | <a href="wiki.pl?action=editprefs">Preferences</a> | 
<hr>The page you are reading now has Wiki-added controls at the top and bottom of the page. The logo is just there for modest visual interest, and to prove that it's possible to use graphics in a Wiki. The top controls are:
<UL>
<li> Page Title (<b>Page Viewer Controls</b> on this page)
<UL>
<li> The Page Title is generated from the link that creates the page.
<li> Clicking on the Page Title shows a list pages on this Wiki that link to this page.
</UL>
<li> HomePage (jump back to home page for this Wiki)
<li> RecentChanges(enter the change-tracking and reporting routines)
<li> Preferences (set username and display and operation preferences)
</UL>
<p>
Except for the Page Title, the same set of controls shows at the bottom of the page. The bottom control set adds:
<UL>
<li> Edit text of this page (bring up the page text in an edit window)
<li> View other revisions (show how the page looked at each step of revision)
<li> Last edited date and time (informational only -- not a control)
<li> diff (show the specific changes performed at each revision step)
</UL>
<p>
All the above functions have (all right -- <b>will</b> have) their own detailed explanation pages elsewhere in this Wiki. Right now, you could just play with them to see what happens, and use your <b>[Back]</b> button to return here.
